" [prev. work] 565b2, 2nd-3rd c.AD: Oppianus Anazarbensis Epicus “Halieutica - Poetae Bucolici et Didactici” 1.380; τὸ λ. 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “ἐπιδημίαι” 3.14, 6.3.16 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; λείη ὑπόστασις a <b>smooth</b> or <b>uniform</b> sediment, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Coac.” 462; [γάλα] λ. καὶ ὁμαλὸν καὶ συνεχὲς ἑαυτῷ 2nd c.AD: Soranus Medicus 1.91. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>smooth, soft</b>, πνεῦμα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 1003 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the sound of the voice, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Politicus” 307a, “Ti.” 67b, “Phlb.” 51d; διάλεκτος 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Po.Herc.” 994.36 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the taste, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-4th c.BC: Timaeus Locrus Philosophus 100ef; also λ. μῦθοι 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 647 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; [τὸ] ἥμερόν τε καὶ λ. [τοῦ ἤθους] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Cratylus” 406a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; λ. πάθημα, opposed to τραχύ, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ti.” 63e; λ. κινήματα τῆς σαρκός 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Fragmenta” 411 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; λ. κίνησις, Cyrenaic phrase for ἡδονή, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD(?): Diogenes Laertius 2.86, compare 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Par.” 10, 3rd c.AD: Alexander Aphrodisiensis Philosophus “in Aristotelis Topicorum libros octo commentaria - pars” 94.32; λ. ἡσυχίη “Anthologia Graeca” 7.278 (1st c.BC: Archias Byzantine)\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; ὡς -οτέρου ἐλέους ὑπάρξοντος (sed to be read τελειοτέρου) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 20.9.11 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; τὸ λ., ={λειότης, τῆς ἑρμηνείας} [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis “de Lysia” 24; τὸ λ. καὶ ὁμαλὲς τῆς συνθέσεως 4th c.BC: Demetrius Phalereus Rhetor “Demetrius on Style” 48. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] <i>adverb</i> λείως <b>smoothly, gently</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 144b, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.384a; καί με κωτίλλοντα λ. τραχὺν ἐκφανεῖν νόον 6th c.BC: Solon Lyricus cited in 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ἀθηναίων Πολιτεία” 12.3. \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>rubbed</b> or <b>ground down</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 1.3, +others, “PHolm.” 19.39; compare λειόω 11: λεῖον, τό \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>], <b>fine sand,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Inscription Délos 500 A 9 (3rd c.BC)\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]. (Prob. λειϝος, cf. Latin <i>lēvis.</i>)","strongNumber":"G3006","accentedUnicode":"λεῖος","shortDef":"smooth, level","mediumDef":"<b>smooth, level, plain,</b> <ref='Luk.3.5'>Lk. 3:5</ref>*","stepGloss":"smooth","stepTransliteration":"leios","count":1,"_es_Definition":"liso, llano","_zh_tw_Definition":"平坦, 平地的 (路 3:5)","_zh_Definition":"平坦, 平地的 (路 3:5)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"bằng phẳng; bằng","_zh_tw_Gloss":"平坦","_es_Gloss":"liso","_zh_Gloss":"平坦"}]}